The paper deals with the problem of computing distances between a pattern and all subwords of a text in the streaming model. This problem involves data structures and algorithms for processing large-scale data, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of $(1\pm\varepsilon)$-approximation, which is a technique commonly used in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The problem of computing distances between strings also involves information theory, which is covered in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also mentions biological data, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category, which includes topics such as bioinformatics. Finally, the problem of computing distances between strings can also be viewed as a problem in computational geometry, which is covered in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category.
